I had the pleasure of meeting up with some of the Chicago Blues and watching the Chelsea game with them. The atmosphere is wonderful for the soccer fan, as they can get just about any game. Our server worked her butt off in the back room, as it was packed by the time our game was underway, and I was more than thrilled that she was able to get them to start the lunch menu half an hour earlier than usual, as I had placed an order for a burger running on Eastern time (pointed at my watch saying lunch started in 15 minutes when in fact lunch normally started at 11:30 *CT*). As for the burger itself, the meat was flavorful, and I had stuck with the standard veggie toppings even though I normally forgo those in favor of just BBQ and bacon. The beer selection is also top notch, with a plethora of craft brewers. For at least the moment, this is my favorite bar in Chicago, and I vow to return, especially for another Chelsea match.
